{
  "texts": [
    "But clearly, the information content of a system does not depend on temperature.",
    "It is not 0 at 0 degrees Kelvin!",
    "Thus, the relation between entropy and information is not direct!",
    "qeios.com doi.org/10.32388/2RBRWN.4Entropy in Infodynamics.",
    "An expansion or re-formulation of the meaning of entropy has its origins in the late 19th and early 20th centuries when, in 1872, the Austrian physicist Ludwig Boltzmann developed a statistical theory of thermodynamics."
  ]
